instruction: Compose a description of the following book.
input: The Catcher in the Rye (by J.D. Salinger)
output: The Catcher in the Rye is a classic coming-of-age novel from 1951 by American author J.D. Salinger. It follows the story of protagonist Holden Caulfield, a troubled teenager trying to make sense of the world around him. Holden's journey reveals many truths about the difficulties of growing up and the struggles of finding one's identity.
